<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 4:02AM EDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...PATCHY DENSE FOG THIS MORNING...
* WHAT...Patchy dense fog with visibility below 1/4 mile.
* WHERE...Area-wide but primarily near area waterways, such as
streams and lakes, with the greatest coverage across southwest
Virginia, northern Plateau, and southwest North Carolina.
* WHEN...Until 9 AM EDT / 8 AM CDT.
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
Drive with caution and be prepared for sudden drop of visibility
due to the fog. Give yourself extra room between you and the
vehicle ahead of you and slow down.</description>
